title: 'We had to wing it': British Airways serves KFC to passengers after issue with in-flight meals
description: Passengers on a British Airways flight were treated to KFC after the airline was unable to provide customers with regular in-flight food.

title: Jordan Henderson's new Saudi Arabian club turns rainbow armband photo black and white
description: Jordan Henderson's new Saudi Arabian football club has turned part of a colour photograph black and white - ensuring his rainbow armband cannot be seen.

title: Teenager 'stable' in hospital after flight home in coma from Spain
description: A teenager put into a coma after developing pneumonia on a family holiday in Spain is back in Scotland after her relatives fundraised more than £80,000 to cover her medical bills and charter a flight home.

title: Is Wagner chief Yevgeny Prigozhin at event with Vladimir Putin in Russia?
description: Wagner Group leader Yevgeny Prigozhin may be at a summit in St Petersburg - where Vladimir Putin is also in attendance, images posted online and in Russian media suggest.

title: Eurozone interest rates return to all-time high
description: The interest rate in the 20 Eurozone countries has been returned to the highest ever level.

title: Kylian Mbappe 'refuses to discuss' world record move to Saudi Arabia
description: Footballer Kylian Mbappe has refused to meet the Saudi Arabian club that has made a world record £257m bid for him, French media has said.

title: Ukrainian troops reportedly break through Russian defences in Zaporizhzhia
description: Ukrainian troops appear to have broken through Russian defensive positions in the south, according to initial reports out of the region.

title: US soldier who entered North Korea is 'not the type to get into trouble', sister says
description: A US soldier who is being held in North Korea after entering the country without permission while on a tourist outing is "not the type to get into trouble", his sister has said.

title: 'Non-human biologics' found at crash sites, former US intelligence official claims
description: "Non-human biologics" were recovered by the US government from crash sites, according to a former US intelligence official.

title: Kim Jong Un shows off banned ballistic missiles to Russia's defence minister
description: Kim Jong Un has showed off banned ballistic missiles to Russia's defence minister during his visit to North Korea.

title: Senate Republican leader freezes mid-sentence during press conference
description: The US Senate Republican leader, Mitch McConnell, appeared to freeze mid-sentence and stare into space for around 20 seconds during a press conference.

title: July was so hot scientists are already confident it is the hottest month ever
description: Scientists are virtually certain that July will be the hottest month ever recorded, even with four days still to go.

title: Military group in Niger claim to have overthrown president
description: A group of soldiers in Niger have claimed to have put an end to the government, hours after detaining President Mohamed Bazoum in the presidential palace.

title: 'Emotionally overwhelming': Girl who vanished at 14 found alive four years later
description: A girl who went missing at the age of 14 has been found four years later, after she walked into a police station and identified herself.

title: 'Miracles do happen': Mother celebrates after girl who vanished walks into police station four years later
description: The mother of a missing girl who was found after four years has said "miracles do happen".
